-- FSA Bans Discretionary Investment Manager Payments to Advisers
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   S c i n t a
-- 2012-10-05T11:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-05/fsa-bans-discretionary-investment-manager-payments-to-advisers.html
The U.K. Financial Services Authority
changed its rules to ensure advisory firms from receiving any
kick-back payments from discretionary investment managers in
exchange for recommending their services.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Scinta at 
 cscinta@bloomberg.net  